In Baba Is Yous brilliant puzzles, rules are meant to be brokenor at least rewritten. Brick wall standing between you and the victory flag? Shift blocks of text to form phrases that change the way the world works. With a few moves, wall is stop becomes wall is pushand success is suddenly within your grasp. Youll marvel as the game responds instantly to your newly created laws. Spell yourself into a corner? Just rewind and retrace your steps. Baba is you, and youre in charge.

editorialNotes.standard: Imagination becomes reality in 5th Cells spectacular puzzlerjust write the name of almost anything in a magical notebook, and it appears before you. Expanding on the more linear Scribblenauts Remix, this game turns you loose to explore an open world. By creating everything from flying pigs to rocket launchers, you solve problems big and small for the people you meet. As the freedom to roam met the freedom to create, we got lost in coming up with the zaniest, most outlandish, or sometimes most diabolical ways to solve each scenario.

editorialNotes.standard: Maze and hidden object genres blend together in Labyrinth City as you guide a French detective through increasingly bizarre crowded spaces. We love the delightful art style and barrage of visual surprises at every turnwere still laughing about that time a ridiculously large banana dropped out of a fruit truck. Dont forget to take your time. The journey is more important than the destination, as this cheery adventure doubles as a celebration of the vibrancy and diversity of city life and the helpfulness of strangers.

editorialNotes.standard: Goofy banter, diverting puzzles, wall-to-wall actionwe couldnt ask for more from a LEGO Ninjago game. Even if youve never seen the Masters of Spinjitzu animated series, these hilarious heroes and their kid-friendly shenanigans are guaranteed to win you over.

With The Room Three, Fireproof Games kept everything we love about this seriesits chilling atmosphere, mind-bending puzzles, and beautiful visualswhile making masterful enhancements. Its no wonder its an Honorable Mention for Best Mobile Game at this years Game Developers Conference. The story continues with trials set by a creepy new nemesis, The Craftsman. A fascinating reinvention of a longtime videogame franchise, Hitman GO takes familiar elements of stealth and assassination and reinterprets them as a wondrously stylized, turn-based boardgame. Each mission presents characters and scenessome from previous Hitman gamesas a sleek diorama, blending old and new to create an innovative experience. Even with helpful distractions and places to hide, inching toward your targets a step at a time demands keen strategy, and trying to pull off optional mission objectives quickly becomes an irresistible obsession.

From the developer that brought the superb board game Carcassonne to iOS comes a fiendishly tricky puzzler thatll test your memory and your reflexes. To clear each set of colorful tiles, youll need to follow specific rules in orderlike removing odd-numbered tiles first, then ones with animalsbefore the clock runs out. Each super-short level is more tense and demanding than the last, making it that much more satisfying when you clean the board and progress to the next challenge.

editorialNotes.standard: In this stunningly original game, you play as a spherical being in a crowded primordial soup, absorbing smaller creatures to grow and avoiding larger ones to survive. Tap to jet across the screen and pursue your prey, but beware: moving reduces your size, making every attack a calculated risk. Osmos delivers a mesmerizing mix of abstract action and physics-based puzzles, with luminescent visuals and an ambient soundtrack that immerse you in another world.

editorialNotes.standard: Donut County is an absolute treat. You drag holes across land to collect bigger and bigger aboveground objects, from puddles and fire pits to trees and boulders. New ideas change gameplay in intriguing ways, and concepts never overstay their welcome, making every puzzle feel new and interesting. The consequences of every hole you control propel a wonderfully quirky story about a suddenly subterranean society seeking a return to the surface. Along with the games fantastic visual style and marvelous soundtrack, its every idiosyncrasy miraculously blends into an inviting, cohesive whole.
editorialNotes.short: Geneva Hodgson: Story editor, Donut County

A rare kind of triumph, Prune takes a simple ideapruning treesand shapes it into a creative, deeply playable puzzle game. The visuals echo the style of Japanese painting in striking fashion, and the beautiful music instills a contemplative tone as you swipe to trim the limbs of a rapidly growing tree and guide it around obstacles. Theres no frantic pace, no demanding skills to masteronly a quietly bewitching and unforgettable experience.
editorialNotes.short: A contemplative and creative experience - trimming trees has never been so beautiful.

Human Resource Machine wraps computer logic fundamentals inside a wonderful, whimsical puzzle game, full of cartoon conveyer belts and demanding managers. Its so much fun you might not realize how much knowledge youre soaking up.

Railbounds tough puzzles are brilliantly focused. Youre given only a handful of rail tiles to guide train cars to the correct destinations in the correct order, and yet even with limited options the potential solutions feel limitless. Do you lay track so Car 4 goes through a tunnel and waits at a crossing gate for Cars 2 and 3 to pass? Do you create loops to delay Car 2? Do you ignore the crossing gate altogether? Few games make success feel like its always just within reach, even when it isnt. A helpful hint system keeps the difficulty from going completely off the rails.
